  "content": "Even in the ultra-dry Atacama Desert, tiny soil-dwelling nematodes are thriving in surprising diversity. Scientists found that biodiversity increases with moisture and altitude shapes which species survive. In the most extreme zones, many nematodes reproduce asexually   a possible survival advantage. The discovery suggests that life in arid regions may be far richer, and more fragile, than once believed.",
